\par\pard\plain \tx1123\tx1685\tx2246\tx2794\tx3355\tx3917\tx4478\tx5040\tx5602\tx6163\tx6725\fi720\ri-720\sl288\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Naked man standing in the middle of the path. Gaunt, scrawny as a pilgrim, but obviously not one, for where pilgrims valued cleanliness, this man was slathered in dirt. His body was so starved and skinny that whatever personality he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d had was gone to make way for the skull. Only his eyeballs maintained their fullness, and they swiveled in their sockets with an uncanny brightness, darting between Seb and the rest of the Ayramun.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Sun\u8217\'92s up,\u8221\'94 Seb said. A typical outland greeting, but the man did not reply. He traded in his hungry, pleading look for a menacing scowl.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93He\u8217\'92s hungry,\u8221\'94 Motaeh said, and she began to fish around in her pack for a loose morsel he might eat, but Moteah .}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Stay back!\u8221\'94 Elrahet snapped. \u8220\'93His belly!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Sign of Schisol.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Upon seeing their disturbed faces, the man traded in his menacing scowl for a smile.}
